Hungary Ruling Party’s Support Drops, Undecided Rise, Tarki Says

-- B y   Z o l t a n   S i m o n
-- 
2011-03-24T06:49:05Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/hungary-ruling-party-s-support-drops-undecided-rise-tarki-says.html
Hungarian Prime Minister  Viktor Orban ’s ruling Fidesz party continued to lose support this month
as the camp of undecided voters swelled, polling company Tarki
said.  Fidesz had 30 percent backing among all eligible voters,
down from 37 percent in February, Tarki said on its  website . The
ranks of undecided rose to 45 percent in March from 38 percent
the previous month.  Support for the Socialist Party was unchanged at 11
percent. The radical nationalist Jobbik’s support increased to 8
percent from 7 percent while Lehet Mas a Politika’s support was
unchanged at 5 percent.  Tarki surveyed 1,000 voting-age Hungarians. No date or
margin of error was indicated.  To contact the reporter responsible for this story:
Zoltan Simon in Budapest at 
 zsimon@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Willy Morris at 
 wmorris@bloomberg.net . 